Anonymous Mon 05 Feb 2024 21:13:23 No.63100839 Report
Quoted By: >>63102692
>>63092255
Adhg, plague ridden rodents, and the green text format ain't my thing, but I gave it a read.
I wanted to give some genuine feedback since you seem to write a lot, and I assume that means you enjoy it.
If you're just trying to write mindless smut, disregard this entire comment, since it's more aimed at general storytelling.
Firstly, perspective. Please for the love of God try to keep it relatively consistent. The story opens with knowledge that only character B has, being told from the perspective of character A. Later, the transitions are quite jarring, and random.
Second, there's very little in the way of description. I can tell the general idea of who looks like what, but locations suffer. "Somewhere north" is not a description of the landscape. While generic descriptions like "in a cave" or "in a forest" work to set a scene, a few lines describing a setting go a long way.
Third, tone. The characters don't seem to take things seriously, so the reader can't really take them seriously. "Golly gee, guess I'll be eaten alive, and my soul will be devoured by daemons for all eternity. What a shame." Is good for humor writing and light tones, but ultimately it kills any and all tension.
Fourth, our hero is joe average. I for one, am a huge fan of joe average as a character. He's relatable, easy to write, and generally tends to be a nice guy. The issue that Joe average often has, and that I think he has in your story, is that he's a cardboard cutout of a character
Lastly, I think you're going for the "insane evil genius" archetype for the rat. I'm not sure if making them seem stupid was intended, but when the maniac fumbles the ball at every point, and maintains the "oh golly gee, guess I lost everything I ever owned again" schtick, they come off as a troglodyte.
Again, if you're going for a goofy story, or for brainless, contrived smut scenarios, then this can be disregarded. If not, I hope you add more flavor to the setting, and character to the characters.
